Class DiscoveryDocument, DiscoveryDocument load(String)

Executes a request for the JSON-formatted discovery document based on the 0.1 version of the API by the given name.

Most API's do not have a 0.1 version, so this will usually fail to return any service documents. @param apiName API name @return discovery document @throws IOException I/O exception executing request

Class JsonCParser

Parses HTTP JSON-C response content into an data class of key/value pairs, assuming the data is wrapped in a {@code "data"} envelope.

Sample usage: 

 
 static void setParser(GoogleTransport transport) {
   transport.addParser(new JsonCParser());
 }
@since 1.0 @author Yaniv Inbar
Class JsonCParser, JsonParser parserForResponse(HttpResponse)

Returns a JSON parser to use for parsing the given HTTP response, skipped over the {@code "data"} envelope.

The parser will be closed if any throwable is thrown. The current token will be the value of the {@code "data"} key. @param response HTTP response @return JSON parser @throws IllegalArgumentException if content type is not Json.CONTENT_TYPE or if {@code "data"} key is not found @throws IOException I/O exception
